additional_info.race_comment: AMERICAN HAMMER (10) resumes from a spell of eight months after showing good ability in a two-start maiden campaign, finishing runner up on debut before a Ballarat win. Draws the back row but will be ready to go off two recent trial wins. KARUMA KEV (1) hasn't had much luck since a win here three back as he was held up in his next outing then sat parked last start. The ace draw could see him turn his fortunes around. POLLY PEACHUM (8) scored back-to-back wins last month and has claims off a good effort last time out when third at Charlton. OUR ROCKY (6) is worth keeping safe resuming for a new yard.
